      en: {
        metaTitle: "Taxi Annemasse → Lyon | Fixed price from €185 | TaxiNeo",
        metaDescription: "Taxi Annemasse → Lyon. 155 km, 1h40, from €185. From the Genevois to France's gastronomic capital via A41/A43. Book 24/7.",
        heroTitle: "Taxi Annemasse → Lyon",
        heroSubtitle: "Your Annemasse → Lyon transfer at €185 — €235. 155 km from the Lake Geneva basin to France's food capital.",
        description: "Lyon, France's gastronomic capital and UNESCO World Heritage city, is 1h40 from Annemasse by motorway.",
        routeDescription: "The route takes the A41 via Annecy then the A43 via Chambéry and Bourgoin-Jallieu to Lyon.",
        introduction: "The taxi from Annemasse to Lyon connects the Swiss border to France's third-largest city, crossing some of the finest landscapes in the Auvergne-Rhone-Alpes region. Annemasse, a Haute-Savoie city welded to Geneva by geography and economy, is the ideal departure point for cross-border workers, Swiss transit travellers and Genevois residents heading to Lyon for business, leisure or rail and air connections. The town, overlooked by the Saleve's impressive cliffs rising like a natural wall between France and the Geneva basin, lives to the rhythm of the cross-border Grand Geneve while keeping its Savoyard roots. The journey first crosses the Genevois savoyard with its gentle hills, then skirts Annecy and its turquoise lake, passes through the Chambery gap alongside Lac du Bourget — France's largest natural lake — before descending the Rhone valley through the Bugey and Nord-Isere. Lyon, at the confluence of the Rhone and Saone, is a UNESCO World Heritage city celebrated for its Vieux-Lyon traboules, Fourviere basilica, Halles Paul Bocuse and iconic bouchons lyonnais.",
        itineraire: "Your driver leaves Annemasse via the A41 junction towards Annecy. The motorway crosses the Genevois savoyard with the majestic Saleve on the right, passes Cruseilles and the spectacular Pont de la Caille above the Usses gorge. After Annecy, the A41 continues south towards Chambery through the Leschaux tunnel. At Chambery, you join the A43 which skirts Lac du Bourget — France's largest natural lake — then crosses the Avant-Pays savoyard and Nord-Isere via Les Abrets and Bourgoin-Jallieu. Arrival in Lyon from the east, with the Part-Dieu skyline and Fourviere hill ahead. Total tolls about €16 (included). Allow 1h40 normally, 2h-2h10 in heavy traffic, especially around Lyon at peak hours and during holiday departures.",
        conseils: "For an early departure from Annemasse, avoid the 7:30-9am window when cross-border commuters clog roads around the town. Leaving before 7am or after 9:30am ensures a smooth journey. Plan a mid-journey break at the Chambery rest area if desired. In Lyon, be dropped in Vieux-Lyon to discover the traboules — Renaissance secret passages between rue Saint-Jean and rue du Boeuf (free, push the carriage doors). Les Halles Paul Bocuse (102 cours Lafayette) is Lyon's gastronomy temple. The Fourviere basilica (free, funicular €3.10 return) offers exceptional city and Alps views in clear weather. If connecting at Part-Dieu station for a TGV, specify when booking and your driver will drop you at the departures hall.",
        comparaisonTransport: "The TER Annemasse — Lyon via Bellegarde or Annecy takes 2h30-3h30 with connection(s) for €25-40. Flixbus takes 3-4h. The TaxiNeo taxi at €185 — €235 is direct door-to-door in 1h40 with no connections. For 3-4 passengers (€46-78/person), the per-person price is comparable to train and the time saving is considerable.",
        faq: [
          { question: "How much is Annemasse — Lyon?", answer: "€185 — €235 depending on exact Lyon address. Fixed guaranteed fare, tolls included." },
          { question: "How long is the journey?", answer: "About 1h40 normally, 2h-2h10 in heavy traffic." },
          { question: "Taxi to Part-Dieu station?", answer: "Yes, direct drop-off at Lyon Part-Dieu or Perrache station, your choice." },
          { question: "And Lyon-Saint Exupéry airport?", answer: "Yes, transfer to LYS airport possible (30 min east of Lyon). Fare may be slightly adjusted." },
          { question: "Can we stop en route?", answer: "Yes, a 10-15 min break is possible mid-journey (e.g. Chambéry rest area). Mention when booking." }
        ],
      },
